, to the unsuccessful Islamist resistance against the military coup, to the Rabaa massacre and the shrinking spaces for protest under Al-Sisi's authoritarian rule, to the resurgence of popular resistance in the shape the Tiran and Sanafir island campaign, it investigates the rise and fall of different coalitions of contenders and explores their impact on Egypt's political transition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aProtest movementszEgypt. 4aConflict and Peace. 4aContemporary History. 4aEgypt. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aRevolutionary groups and movements. 4aRevolutions, uprisings, rebellions. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 21st Century.2bisacsh  aSocial Movements, Protest, Repression, Egypt, Arab Spring.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048553457zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048553457zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048553457/original  a978-3-11-076709-4 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA